North Mahaska School
August 24 at 11:42 AM ·

Due to the projected excessive heat for Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday, NM Schools will NOT begin until Monday, August 31. CDC guidance states that fans should not be used in classrooms. Along with the recommendations to wear masks when social distancing is not possible, the administration has determined that it is in the best interest for NM to postpone the start of school until Monday, August 31. The football game this Friday night vs. East Marshall will be held.

Warhawks, come grab a mask tonight from 6-7PM at the high school canopy!

These masks are super light, breathable fabric, and very comfortable (trust Mrs. Nelson, she has tried lots of masks)! Mrs. Nelson is wearing an adult s/m (this is a snug fit, it would fit youth probably 10+).

Sizes available tonight are adult l/xl (not a lot bigger than the s/m, but a little more room), youth 3-7 (probably best for PK-K and some 1st graders), and youth 7-12 (probably great for 2nd-3rd grade and some 4th graders). We sold out of adult s/m today, but if you would like one, please stop tonight to pre-order and pay!

post_text: WARHAWKS! North Mahaska is ready to get back to school! With social distancing measures in place, we know school will look just a little bit different this year! The recommendation is that student desks are placed 6 feet apart. However, we know that building positive relationships and collaborative learning has always been a focus at NM and that focus will continue. These desk barriers will allow students to continue to work together safely. At this time, NM PACT is working with NM teachers to fund raise for these barriers for each student. Please share far and wide! Warhawks want to go back to school and stay in school!

People are amazing, and NM is blessed to have great people and businesses that care about our kids! We met our goal within an hour for the 10 desks requested (plus one extra desk -- a total of $1,000!), but let’s see how many more desks we can purchase to fill both classrooms with these desks that are so desperately needed!!! The teachers were trying to make use of the funds in the best way possible and only requested a half of what was needed. Help us reach our NEW goal! (Remember...these donations are tax-deductible! Attention Warhawks!

We are unable to have our physical bookfair this year due to the COVID-19 pandemic. However, we are excited to be able to offer an ONLINE option! At this time, when many of us are at home, we can all use a good book. Scholastic has books at all price ranges, many being very affordable. All profits will go directly toward free books for our school and back to support our students in the classroom.

All orders will ship directly to your home. It was my understanding that book orders over $25 will ship free. You may also order kits and resources, however, shipping will be charged for those items. If you would like to place a second order for those items, it will be cheaper to only pay shipping for those items and get free shipping for your book order if it is over $25. Please let us know if you have any questions!

https://www.scholastic.com/bf/northmahaska

Hello all,
Due to today's school closure, we will be meeting remotely via Google Meet. This is our first time using this, so please be patient with us! We do ask that you join if possible as we try this new platform. Many people have difficulty getting to meetings and if this works, we could use this more often.

At this time I cannot schedule a meeting, so at 5:30 I will start the meeting and share the link to the meeting to give you time to get familiar with logging in. At that time you will probably see a blank screen as I will not be online yet. The meeting will start at 6PM.

Thank you for your patience!

NM PACT will be sponsoring a BOWLING event for North Mahaska Boys!

Statesmen Lanes (Mahaska Bowl)
Saturday, March 21 from 2PM-4PM
**Games will be free of charge, paid for by NM PACT (Donations Welcome)**
Concessions will be available for purchase.

Boys may come and bring a special adult female. This event will be able to accommodate 96 people at one time. It will be first come, first served. Attendees are not expected to stay the whole time, so if lanes are full, guests may wait for a lane to open up.

Spread the word and watch for a flyer to come home from school as well!

North Mahaska School Board Elections will be held with the general election on Tuesday, November 5th.

Seats open for re-election:
District 1: Michelle Sampson and James Roach (one seat available)
District 2: Dirk Wilkin, Incumbent (running unopposed)
District 3: Keith Foster, Incumbent and Erica Groom (one seat available)

Three questions were emailed to each candidate from NMEA members on Tuesday. Responses were requested by Friday evening. A second email was sent on Saturday with a deadline of Sunday at 3:00pm for responses to be published in the local paper.

We will publish the questions asked by NMEA and the answers from each candidate who responded here on NM PACT's Facebook page as well!

post_text: While having a conversation recently with a North Mahaska citizen, I was told, “Why does the school need air conditioning? I didn’t have it when I went to school.” Here is why: The classroom’s environment can affect a student’s learning process by as much as 25 percent. Further, high classroom temps create a 12.3 percent likelihood of failing a subject exam. When people moving to the community look at schools, they DO pay attention to where our school ranks in the state, as far as testing scores. Plus, making a comfortable environment for our educators will only create a better learning experience for our children. ❤️🖤

post_text:
Things to know for election day:

1. Polls are open from 7am-8pm on Tuesday, September 10th in the North Mahaska elementary cafeteria. Please enter through the south door of the cafeteria (location will marked). Do not use the office entrances.

2. Parking will be available in the south parking lot.

3. You can still vote at the polls if you requested an absentee ballot, but did not send it back. Take the ballot to the poll and surrender it. You will then be able to vote at the polls.

4. If you have moved since the last election, bring your current picture ID with your current address with you.

5. You CAN register to vote on election day. Bring proof of identity and residency. The best form is a valid driver's license with your current address. If you cannot prove residency or identity, another registered voter in your precinct may attest you your identity and residency. That person must have a current photo ID.

post_text:
Reminder: Walk-A-Thon address forms are due on Friday!

This year, the forms changed slightly. On the left side, please fill out the complete address. On the right, write who the request is to and from. We will cut these out and put them in with each donation request we send, along with however many feet is needed. For example: two children’s names in the from line indicate that two feet should be sent! This helps reduce postage and to ensure all children can receive a foot from a family member.

In addition, please complete as many addresses as possible. If you have two children, please fill out each form with both kids’ names on each one. For example: I have two children, therefore we completed 12 addresses with our kids’ names on all of them.

We thank you in advance, this is the largest fundraiser of the year and is run completely by volunteers!

post_text:
As parents, we would move mountains to ensure the safety of our children. I’m sure most other parents would be right there with us. The proposed improvements to the school will be one way we can help ensure safety with secure entrances, storm shelter, and eliminating the need to open windows to cool down the building.

We also try to make a comfortable learning environment at home with rules, expectations, and comfort. Why wouldn’t we do what we can to help that at school for our kids too? When our daughter was asked to make three wishes on the first day of 2nd grade her FIRST wish was to have air conditioning in the school! Kids learn better when they’re comfortable (not to mention the teachers too!)

Please join us in VOTING YES on September 10 at the school. —Nick and Laura Anderson

post_text:
When our oldest son, in the class of 2022, started kindergarten, we didn’t live in New Sharon, but we open-enrolled him to North Mahaska because it had what we were looking for in a school district. We are blessed to have small classes, great teachers, and one of the strongest communities around.

We have since moved to the district, and got our bond referendum literature in the mail this week. We read it. Did you?

Even with everything our district has going for it, we can do better for our kids. The proposed safety and security improvements are benefits to students for generations to come. The fact that these improvements can be done without increasing our tax rates is a win/win!

We have another future Warhawk who will be entering in 2022 and can say without a doubt we will be voting yes on September 10th.

We hope you will too.

-Bryon and Christy Bellinger

post_text: My name is Carrie Kral and my family and I live in New Sharon. We have an upcoming 5th grader at North Mahaska and a future little Warhawk. I am a graduate of North Mahaska, as well as a parent, and President of our elementary PTO. North Mahaska is such an amazing district that has so many benefits, but schools are also supposed to be a safe and secure place for our children. They are an essential part of our future and it's important they receive the best education possible. With that being said, there is no doubt in my mind my husband and I will be voting YES for North Mahaska's School Bond Referendum for safety and security. Knowing that our school has the chance to increase safety and security as well as maintain a comfortable learning and working environment with new HVAC for our students and staff is key. We have the opportunity to improve this community starting with our children and grandchildren. Please consider voting yes on September 10, and invest in improving not only our school but our future!

We are excited to offer our support by voting YES! on September 10th!

Stacie Johannes

Hey families!

Scholastic has made shopping at the book fair MUCH easier. The new e-wallet system is a secure way for parents to load money into an account for your child to shop at the book fair (NO CASH NEEDED!!).

You simply log-in, enter your card information, set a dollar limit for your child, and you're done! When they come to the book fair, we look up their name when they check-out and charge that amount to your card. They can not spend over the dollar amount you have chosen and your card isn't charged until they shop, so if they don't spend it all, you won't get charged!

Go to http://www.scholastic.com/bf/northmahaska to get your child's account set up!

shared_text:
East Market Grocery And Deli
April 22, 2019 at 9:10 AM ·

****Attention North Mahaska Parents,****** or whomever may join your child for this special event. This Friday, April 26 at 11:30 is lunch on the lawn with elementary students. So...after last year, not being prepared, people having to wait, running out of items. This year we want to be prepared. We ask if you can, please give us your order the day before, (or earlier would be great). That way we can have more of an idea what we need, have enough sub bread baked that morning, etc. Then we can have it ready for you. You can even pay ahead of time, grab and go. (Don't forget drinks). If you are ordering fryer food. Same thing. We can have it ready for you. Friday is our small loin special. (Small loin and French fries for $5.00).
Thank you so much. With your help this year it should be alot smoother ;)

One of our favorites is coming soon.... THE BOOK FAIR! We are hopeful that our early release of our Book Fair schedule will provide more opportunities for our volunteers to find a time that will work to help!

This book fair is a great way for our organization to raise funds for North Mahaska Elementary and get free books for our students!

Projects we have funded this year include: Charlotte's Web Day, Polar Express Day, purchasing science materials for classrooms, purchasing fabric for classroom projects (blankets were made to donate to babies in the hospital), purchasing recorders for all students in 4th grade (you're welcome parents, HA!), and MANY more!

We cannot do all these things without your help. We thank you from the bottom of our hearts in advance for volunteering! NM is a great place to be!

Our teachers and Nurse Julie do so much for our kiddos already. Let’s not make them spend their own money for supplies! ❤️

post_text:
North Mahaska Schools are now accepting open enrollment applications for the 2019-2020 school year!
Below are some FAQs:
1. Can any student out of district open enroll to North Mahaska Schools?
-Yes, students in grades K-12 can submit an open enrollment application. The application must be submitted by March 1, 2019. For students entering kindergarten in the fall of 2018, the open enrollment application is due September 1, 2019. Out of district preschool students can attend North Mahaska Schools without submitting an open enrollment application.
2. Is transportation provided for out of district students?
-Yes, however, the North Mahaska CSD buses cannot cross into another school district to pick students up for school. Our buses typically pick up students from outside the district at the dividing line between the two districts.
3. Is there a tuition cost to parents for out of district students attending North Mahaska?
-No, parents do not have to pay tuition. Regular school registration fees apply.

https://vimeo.com/252565587
